Cardio Good Fitness Dataset¶

  • Data Features:

  • Product - the model no. of the treadmill

  • Age - in no of years, of the customer

  • Gender - of the customer

  • Education - in no. of years, of the customer

  • Marital Status - of the customer

  • Usage - Avg. # times the customer wants to use the treadmill every week

  • Fitness - Self rated fitness score of the customer (5 - very fit, 1 - very unfit)

  • Income - of the customer

  • Miles- expected to run

Plotting the summary mean,mode,median using histogram for Miles Variable¶
In [160]:
mean=cardio['Miles'].mean()
median=cardio['Miles'].median()
mode=cardio['Miles'].mode()

print('Mean: ',mean,'\nMedian: ',median,'\nMode: ',mode[0]) # Printing the Mean, Median, Mode values with label

plt.figure(figsize=(12,6)) # Figure size is set
plt.hist(cardio['Miles'],bins=100,color='hotpink') #Histogram is plotted

plt.axvline(mean,color='darkgreen',label='Mean')     
plt.axvline(median,color='darkblue',label='Median')
plt.axvline(mode[0],color='yellow',label='Mode1')

plt.xlabel('Miles')   # labelling x-axis
plt.ylabel('Frequency')   # labelling y-axis
plt.legend()              # Plotting the legend
plt.show()

Mean:  103.19444444444444 
Median:  94.0 
Mode:  85
Observations:¶

Distribution is Positively Skewed since Mean > Median > Mode

Insights & Recommendations¶

Product Insights for TM195, TM498 & TM195¶

  • Product TM195 is the most Popular model
  • Highest Age of Customer usign Model TM195 is 50 years
  • The mean miles run by Product TM195 is the lowest among other two products
  • Lower Income Customers are inclined to buy Product TM195
  • Average age of buying Product TM195 is the lowest
  • Product TM798 is preferred by Customers who have more no. of years of education(viz. > 16 years)
  • Product TM195 & TM498 is preferred by Customers who have less no. of years of education(viz. education < 16 years)
  • The usage of Product TM195 is mostly 3-4 times a week
  • TM195 are used by both Male & Female equally
  • Higher Income Customers prefer to use TM798 over other Products
  • Both Gender Customers who are using Model No. TM798 have a longer run distribution of miles run viz. Around 100 to 300 miles
  • Product 195 & 498 have a varied distribution of miles starting from least number of miles till around 200 miles
  • Product 798 is least sold product. Only 40 out of 180 Customers purchased it(i.e. 22.22%)
  • Customers whose Gender is Male prefer to use Model No. TM 195 & TM498 whose Run Miles are less than 100. And Model. TM 798 for run Miles more than 150
  • Customers whose Gender is Female prefer Model No. TM 195 & TM 498 over Model No. TM 798

General Data Insights(would be useful for Customer Segmentation and appropriate Advertising)¶

  • Age Density in Dataset is 20-30 years
  • Customers Education most distribution in dataset is 14-16 years
  • Customers Incomemost distribution in dataset is 45000-60000
  • Most of the Customers will run around 60-120 Miles
  • Customers prefer to use Treadmill 3-4 times a week

Recommendations¶

  • Product TM798 should be adverstised more as luxurious product to be targeted for Customers who are more Educated, who have more Income(good Correlation with Education)
  • Product TM195 & Product TM498 is more of a budget product and targeted for Customers who income is around 30000 to 60000 dollars
  • Company should Advertise that Customers who plan to run from 100 to 300 Miles should buy TM798 & Customers whose Average plan to run is around 200 Miles should buy either TM195 or TM498
  • Product TM798 should be special advertised for Customers who are Partnered
  • Special Promotional offers should be run by the company for Mens day, Father's Day, Brother's Day since Men use Treadmill more than Women
  • Based on the analysis Product TM195 & TM498 should be advertised and discounts/incentives should be provided to Customers whose Gender is Female
